<p>That means the max velocity requested could be as high as 4.24 m/s, since <code>sqrt(3^2 + 3^2) = 4.24</code>.</p>
<p>We initially had separate pid controllers for x and y, but later found that it was better to have a single <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller that used the distance as the process variable (error), and then had our robot just drive at the correct angle to get to the target. You can use the builtin wpilib classes to do the vector math for you</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2025-10-06T23:02:54.032Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":209,"readers_count":208,"score":91.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":506919,"topic_slug":"best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose","display_username":"Tim Winters","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":19820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"78 AIR Strike Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose/506919/3","custom_user_title":"78 AIR Strike Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":3}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":3,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3756655,"name":"Eric Huang","username":"erichuang","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/eb8c5e/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-10-06T23:20:58.713Z","cooked":"<p>We currently aren’t using any acceleration gain for our drive motors. I’ll definitely try adding that tomorrow, along with testing just with feedforward! Thanks!</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2025-10-06T23:20:58.713Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":187,"readers_count":186,"score":62.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":506919,"topic_slug":"best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose","display_username":"Eric Huang","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":53190,"username":"truher","name":"joel truher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/truher/{size}/172222_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61986,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4122 Co-President"},"post_url":"/t/best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose/506919/4","custom_user_title":"4122 Co-President","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3757064,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2025-10-07T16:50:41.616Z","cooked":"<p>My guess is (and the feedforward will address) is that static friction (the minimum amount required of velocity/voltage to move the robot) is causing issues with your <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> tuning.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">
        // apply PID control
        double velX = m_xPID.calculate(distX);
        double velY = m_yPID.calculate(distY);

        // prepare static friction
        double sX = Math.copySign(kS, velX);
        double sY = Math.copySign(kS, velY);

        // add static friction
        velX += sX;
        velY += sY;

        // clamp output
        velX = -MathUtil.clamp(velX, -1.0, 1.0);
        velY = -MathUtil.clamp(velY, -1.0, 1.0);

        // drive!
        m_drivetrain.setControl(m_drive
                .withForwardPerspective(ForwardPerspectiveValue.BlueAlliance)
                .withVelocityX(velX) // Drive forward with negative Y(forward)
                .withVelocityY(velY) // Drive left with negative X (left)
                .withTargetDirection(m_targetPose.getRotation()));
</code></pre>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2025-10-07T16:50:41.616Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":113,"readers_count":112,"score":22.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":506919,"topic_slug":"best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":61986,"username":"erichuang","name":"Eric Huang","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/eb8c5e/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":36169,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/best-way-to-implement-go-to-pose/506919/5","custom_user_title":"Software Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3757110,"name":"Val","username":"Otter502","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/otter502/{size}/245799_2.png","created_at":"2025-10-07T17:54:49.414Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="erichuang" data-post="1" data-topic="506919">
